actual.comment:
According to the Biosphere Territory “Issyk-Kul” and volunteered inspectors, the following data on prosecution of illegal hunting in the Project area have been obtained:


(i) the first half of 2014 (January-June), 24 violations were registered (out of which 17  - illegal hunting, 7 - illegal logging) of total collected penalty of 2,500 USD;


(ii) the first half of 2015 (January-June), 51 violations were registered (of which 21 illegal hunting, 15 illegal logging and 15 other cases) of total penalty collected of 14,255 USD;


(iii) the second half of the 2014 (July-December), 14 violations were registered (of which 7 illegal hunting, 5 illegal logging and 2 other cases) of total penalty collected of 3,399 USD;


During the first half of 2015, 51 violations were detected for a total amount 14,255 USD; first half of 2014, 24 violations were detected for a total amount 2,500 USD. 

Thus the detecting rate has been increased from 24 to 51 and the penalties amount from 2,500 USD to 14,255USD compared to the previous period.


In total, during this reporting period  (the second half of the 2014 and the first half of 2015) 65 violations cases of the nature conservation legislations were recorded (out of 28 cases on illegal hunting, 20 cases on illegal logging and 17 other cases for carrying hunting weapons, etc.) for the total penalty amount of 17,654 USD. 


The Project enhanced the capacity of the Biosphere Territory “Issyk-Kel”, “Karakol” Nature State Park  of SAEPF rangers and freelance inspectors through trainings, workshops on involving local communities for awareness raising, biodiversity conservation activities and conducting wildlife monitoring. 


The Project purchased and provided a group of volunteer inspectors with uniforms and equipment (tent, portable radio set, GPS navigator, binoculars etc.) for monitoring and conservation of wildlife and supported the anti-poaching activities of Biosphere Territory “Issyk-Kel” rangers.


Department on Nature Resources Regulation passed the order in August, 2014 to temporarily ban (until 2016) game and sport hunting of all ungulate species in several regions of Kyrgyzstan including all districts of the Issyk-Kul region.
